00:59:22,347 --> 00:59:24,679
there's a human response
that makes it undeniable

1015
00:59:24,749 --> 00:59:27,309
that I'm connecting
with an intelligent being.

1016
00:59:29,654 --> 00:59:33,146
Science has been tantalized for years
at the prospect of talking

1017
00:59:33,225 --> 00:59:35,250
to the most intelligent
creatures on earth,

1018
00:59:35,327 --> 00:59:36,760
which may not be human beings.

1019
00:59:36,828 --> 00:59:38,227
A small group of scientists

1020
00:59:38,296 --> 00:59:40,628
determined to see
if humans and dolphins

1021
00:59:40,699 --> 00:59:42,257
can learn to talk to each other.

1022
00:59:42,334 --> 00:59:47,135
We keep spending billions of dollars
for sending signals up into the sky,

1023
00:59:47,205 --> 00:59:48,638
and we have a species here

1024
00:59:48,707 --> 00:59:52,473
that can conceivably be
more intelligent than we are.

1025
01:00:01,353 --> 01:00:04,413
Dolphins can understand
how to manipulate situations,

1026
01:00:04,489 --> 01:00:05,854
how to relate to people,

1027
01:00:05,924 --> 01:00:10,520
how to create innovatively
out of their own imagination.

1028
01:00:10,595 --> 01:00:11,892
It sometimes amazes me

1029
01:00:11,963 --> 01:00:13,555
that the only language

1030
01:00:13,632 --> 01:00:15,793
which has been extensively
taught to dolphins

1031
01:00:15,867 --> 01:00:17,892
is a version of
American Sign Language,

1032
01:00:17,969 --> 01:00:19,368
which, of course,
you use your hands,

1033
01:00:19,437 --> 01:00:21,200
so you have
all these wonderful signals,

1034
01:00:21,273 --> 01:00:24,071
and people use their hands
to give messages to dolphins.

1035
01:00:25,644 --> 01:00:27,703
And this somehow
kind of misses the point

1036
01:00:27,779 --> 01:00:29,872
because dolphins don't have hands,

1037
01:00:29,948 --> 01:00:32,883
so this is inherently
a very one-way process.

1038
01:00:32,951 --> 01:00:34,680
And it's this anthropomorphic

1039
01:00:34,753 --> 01:00:37,586
"We have something
to teach them or control them,"

1040
01:00:37,656 --> 01:00:40,682
and perhaps we ought to be looking
at what they can give to us.

1041
01:00:43,395 --> 01:00:45,920
It's not about intelligence.

1042
01:00:45,997 --> 01:00:48,659
It's about consciousness.

1043
01:00:48,733 --> 01:00:53,170
They are self-aware,
like humans are self-aware.

1044
01:00:53,238 --> 01:00:55,069
That means that we look in the mirror,

1045
01:00:55,140 --> 01:00:58,075
and we know exactly
what we're looking at.

1046
01:00:58,143 --> 01:01:02,239
I don't believe that the fishermen
here are aware of that.

1047
01:01:07,085 --> 01:01:08,677
When they're in that killing cove

1048
01:01:08,753 --> 01:01:11,881
and their babies are being
slaughtered in front of them,

1049
01:01:11,957 --> 01:01:13,549
they're aware of that.

1050
01:01:13,625 --> 01:01:17,857
They can anticipate
what's going to happen to them.

1051
01:02:03,441 --> 01:02:07,810
The first time I went to Taiji
was in 1980,

1052
01:02:07,879 --> 01:02:11,246
and I had been to Iki the year before.

1053
01:02:11,316 --> 01:02:15,343
Iki is a tourist destination for Japanese

1054
01:02:15,420 --> 01:02:17,354
which became infamous

1055
01:02:17,422 --> 01:02:21,153
for this... most ghastly
slaughters of dolphins.

1056
01:02:21,226 --> 01:02:24,855
I mean, literally thousands of them
would... could be killed in a day.

1057
01:02:28,933 --> 01:02:33,165
Well, I went back to Iki
about three years ago,

1058
01:02:33,238 --> 01:02:35,001
and they don't have any dolphins,

1059
01:02:35,073 --> 01:02:39,908
where once they had thousands of them
streaming by the coast.

1060
01:02:48,053 --> 01:02:49,816
Irony of ironies.

1061
01:02:49,888 --> 01:02:54,291
Because the international
captivity trade is so lucrative,

1062
01:02:54,359 --> 01:02:56,418
they want to be in on it,

1063
01:02:56,494 --> 01:02:59,463
and they don't have any dolphins.

1064
01:03:01,199 --> 01:03:03,394
They have to have dolphins
for their dolphin parks,

1065
01:03:03,468 --> 01:03:06,369
so they go buy them in Taiji now.

1066
01:03:08,907 --> 01:03:12,070
Every cetacean known to man
is endangered

1067
01:03:12,143 --> 01:03:14,202
just by going anywhere near Japan.

1068
01:03:18,350 --> 01:03:22,753
We asked the Taiji fishermen
if we could subsidize this activity...

1069
01:03:22,821 --> 01:03:25,585
in other words, if you leave the boats
tied up at the dock,

1070
01:03:25,657 --> 01:03:27,625
we'll pay you the same amount of money

1071
01:03:27,692 --> 01:03:31,753
you would have made
killing dolphins in Taiji.

1072
01:03:31,830 --> 01:03:35,095
They got back to us and said
"It's not about money.

1073
01:03:35,166 --> 01:03:38,329
It's about pest control."

1074
01:03:38,403 --> 01:03:39,700
Pest control.

1075
01:03:39,771 --> 01:03:41,796
In other words,

1076
01:03:41,873 --> 01:03:44,364
they're being told by the government

1077
01:03:44,442 --> 01:03:49,277
that the dolphin are
eating too much fish in the ocean.

1078
01:03:57,455 --> 01:04:03,451
This is not attempt
just to incriminate whales as a bad guy.

1079
01:04:03,528 --> 01:04:09,228
However, we cannot ignore
the fishing effort has been decreasing.

1080
01:04:09,300 --> 01:04:15,068
It's seriously hard to take that
PowerPoint demonstration seriously.

1081
01:04:15,140 --> 01:04:19,304
I have to tell you
that there is very strong evidence

1082
01:04:19,377 --> 01:04:23,143
that whales are consuming
huge quantities of fish

1083
01:04:23,214 --> 01:04:26,115
that are also the target of fisheries.

1084
01:04:26,184 --> 01:04:28,482
The Government of Brazil
wants to put on record

1085
01:04:28,553 --> 01:04:30,487
that to us it certainly amounts

1086
01:04:30,555 --> 01:04:33,581
to what only can be described
as biological nonsense.

1087
01:04:33,658 --> 01:04:36,126
It is clear that the fisheries
of the world are on decline,

1088
01:04:36,194 --> 01:04:39,095
and the obvious culprit is people,

1089
01:04:39,164 --> 01:04:41,689
and we don't want to acknowledge that.

1090
01:04:50,475 --> 01:04:54,468
We look at the ocean
as a source of infinite quality seafood,

1091
01:04:54,546 --> 01:04:56,639
and I think we're learning
some hard lessons

1092
01:04:56,714 --> 01:04:57,976
that this isn't true.

1093
01:05:01,619 --> 01:05:04,315
We're pulling the fish
out of the ocean at such a rate

1094
01:05:04,389 --> 01:05:07,153
and eroding and diminishing
our marine ecosystems

1095
01:05:07,225 --> 01:05:09,955
so bad that the whole
thing could collapse.

1096
01:05:23,508 --> 01:05:26,443
70% of human beings,
seven out of ten people,

1097
01:05:26,511 --> 01:05:29,241
rely as their principal
protein on seafood.

1098
01:05:30,982 --> 01:05:34,418
If we lose access to fish in the sea,

1099
01:05:34,486 --> 01:05:38,445
we will be causing
the biggest public health problem

1100
01:05:38,523 --> 01:05:40,991
human beings have ever faced.

1101
01:05:46,264 --> 01:05:50,462
The Japanese literally control
the world marketplace in fish.

1102
01:05:50,535 --> 01:05:54,471
They have buyers in every
major port in the world.

1103
01:05:54,539 --> 01:05:58,908
They're catching their fish
from an ever-depleting supply,

1104
01:05:58,977 --> 01:06:02,879
and I think they have a real fear
that they will run out of food.

1105
01:06:04,782 --> 01:06:09,014
What more logical thing could they do
than catch whales to replace them?

1106
01:06:10,488 --> 01:06:15,585
International Whaling Commission
is essentially killing

1107
01:06:15,660 --> 01:06:19,994
coastal small-type
whaling communities like Taiji.

1108
01:06:32,076 --> 01:06:37,275
This body should seriously consider
the proposal that is before us.

1109
01:06:37,348 --> 01:06:41,409
Dominica would like to compliment
the Japanese delegation.

1110
01:06:41,486 --> 01:06:43,010
We strongly support the proposal.

1111
01:06:43,087 --> 01:06:46,523
Antigua and Barbuda
supports this declaration in its entirety.

1112
01:06:46,591 --> 01:06:49,116
Do we have any concern, any sympathy

1113
01:06:49,193 --> 01:06:51,058
for the plight of the people of Japan?

1114
01:06:51,129 --> 01:06:53,962
This is an opportunity to help Japan.

1115
01:06:54,032 --> 01:06:57,229
We could help the Japanese cause
and the people of Taiji.

1116
01:06:57,302 --> 01:07:01,204
We therefore urge this IWC to grant...

1117
01:07:01,272 --> 01:07:04,298
...their basic request
for them to engage in whaling.

1118
01:07:04,375 --> 01:07:08,277
And therefore, St. Kitts and Nevis
support this proposal.

1119
01:07:08,346 --> 01:07:09,608
Thank you, Mr. Chairman.

1120
01:07:09,681 --> 01:07:14,744
In my opinion, this has
been sufficient enough time

1121
01:07:14,819 --> 01:07:20,314
to allow for the replenishment
of species... of certain species...

1122
01:07:20,391 --> 01:07:21,585
which were in decline

1123
01:07:21,659 --> 01:07:23,991
and some others which were
nearing extinction.

1124
01:07:24,062 --> 01:07:28,294
There are several facets in the interests
out of Antigua in whaling.

1125
01:07:28,366 --> 01:07:29,663
First of all, the government

1126
01:07:29,734 --> 01:07:31,702
is presently interested
in the whaling commission

1127
01:07:31,769 --> 01:07:34,431
because the Japanese government's
paying them to be interested.

1128
01:07:35,640 --> 01:07:38,040
The Japanese government
and their agencies

1129
01:07:38,109 --> 01:07:41,510
go to small bankrupt nations

1130
01:07:41,579 --> 01:07:44,412
and offer them financial support,

1131
01:07:44,482 --> 01:07:45,972
offer them whatever it takes,

1132
01:07:46,050 --> 01:07:48,678
firstly to get them to join the IWC

1133
01:07:48,753 --> 01:07:51,119
and then, when they get here,
to vote for Japan.

1134
01:07:51,189 --> 01:07:54,420
This is how whaling
in the 21st century works.

1135
01:07:54,492 --> 01:07:56,483
What kind of whales
pass through Antigua?

1136
01:07:56,561 --> 01:07:58,756
We have...

1137
01:07:58,830 --> 01:07:59,990
I think the Commissioner might be...

1138
01:08:00,064 --> 01:08:01,156
I think there's
some humpback whales...

1139
01:08:01,232 --> 01:08:02,256
- Yes.
...that pass through Antigua.

1140
01:08:02,333 --> 01:08:03,527
I'm not sure of the details

1141
01:08:03,601 --> 01:08:04,795
of the whales that pass
through Antigua

1142
01:08:04,869 --> 01:08:06,769
at this point in time,
but there are whales

1143
01:08:06,838 --> 01:08:08,465
that pass through our waters
from time to time.

1144
01:08:08,539 --> 01:08:09,938
I have seen only...

1145
01:08:10,008 --> 01:08:13,341
My only interaction with whales
are what I see on television.

1146
01:08:14,412 --> 01:08:19,714
It is so transparent to even the least
perspicacious onlooker

1147
01:08:19,784 --> 01:08:25,017
that they have prostituted themselves
for a few yen.

1148
01:08:27,425 --> 01:08:31,953
The Japanese government
pays our fees, our annual fees,

1149
01:08:32,030 --> 01:08:35,193
for participation in the International
Whaling Commission.

1150
01:08:35,266 --> 01:08:37,496
It has nothing to do with nutrition.

1151
01:08:37,568 --> 01:08:40,128
It simply has to do with the fact
that "You voted for us,

1152
01:08:40,204 --> 01:08:42,638
"so let's give you something
that you people can see

1153
01:08:42,707 --> 01:08:45,073
"that it was worth your while
to sell your vote to us...

1154
01:08:45,143 --> 01:08:46,371
fisheries complexes."

1155
01:08:49,647 --> 01:08:53,310
Interestingly,
the fisheries complexes built by Japan

1156
01:08:53,384 --> 01:08:54,874
have already gone into disuse

1157
01:08:54,952 --> 01:08:58,547
because it has nothing to do with fishing.

1158
01:08:58,623 --> 01:09:00,386
One neighbor got the goodies,

1159
01:09:00,458 --> 01:09:03,359
and every other neighbor
wants a part of the goodies.

1160
01:09:03,428 --> 01:09:05,692
Every island
in the Eastern Caribbean...

1161
01:09:05,763 --> 01:09:07,890
St. Kitts, Antigua,
St. Vincent., St. Lucia,

1162
01:09:07,965 --> 01:09:09,262
Grenada, Dominica...

1163
01:09:09,333 --> 01:09:11,096
we all have the same goodies.

1164
01:09:12,270 --> 01:09:15,865
In Dominica, we have a $22 million
fisheries complex

1165
01:09:15,940 --> 01:09:19,740
which is used for the local merchants
to store imported chicken.

1166
01:09:22,780 --> 01:09:26,546
It's very sad to see the beautiful
islands in the Caribbean

1167
01:09:26,617 --> 01:09:31,213
becoming neon-lit whorehouses
for the Japanese.

1168
01:09:32,523 --> 01:09:34,718
It really runs counter to logic

1169
01:09:34,792 --> 01:09:36,089
why the Japanese continue

1170
01:09:36,160 --> 01:09:39,687
to keep this dying
whaling business going,

1171
01:09:39,764 --> 01:09:41,698
especially when you get the facts

1172
01:09:41,766 --> 01:09:43,199
about the levels of mercury

1173
01:09:43,267 --> 01:09:45,258
and other contaminants
in the meat.

1174
01:09:45,336 --> 01:09:47,804
I visited Japan earlier this year,

1175
01:09:47,872 --> 01:09:51,205
and I discovered that there
was another peculiar reason

1176
01:09:51,275 --> 01:09:53,709
for the Japanese position
at the IWC.

1177
01:09:53,778 --> 01:09:57,009
This has not got to do
with economics.

1178
01:09:57,081 --> 01:09:59,572
it hasn't even got to do with politics.

1179
01:09:59,650 --> 01:10:02,346
It really has to do with the...

1180
01:10:02,420 --> 01:10:06,720
the remnants
of a traditional notion of empire.

1181
01:10:06,791 --> 01:10:09,351
They had had enough of the West

1182
01:10:09,427 --> 01:10:12,260
telling them what to do
and how to do it and when to do it.

1183
01:10:12,330 --> 01:10:14,696
"Well, you're not going to make us
stop killing whales."

1184
01:10:15,933 --> 01:10:19,960
There's some kind of misplaced
nationalistic pride at work.

1185
01:10:20,037 --> 01:10:22,335
It's an industry that is
massively subsidized

1186
01:10:22,406 --> 01:10:23,634
by Japanese taxpayers,

1187
01:10:23,708 --> 01:10:25,608
and when you have those sorts
of subsidies in place,

1188
01:10:25,676 --> 01:10:27,405
you invite corruption.

1189
01:10:27,478 --> 01:10:31,778
In order to perpetuate
this cultural argument,

1190
01:10:31,849 --> 01:10:33,783
the Taiji dolphin hunters

1191
01:10:33,851 --> 01:10:37,116
started giving
the dolphin meat away free

1192
01:10:37,188 --> 01:10:38,849
to the school system.

1193
01:10:38,923 --> 01:10:41,289
They're getting this
in a form of propaganda.

1194
01:10:41,359 --> 01:10:42,690
They're not being told

1195
01:10:42,760 --> 01:10:45,160
that the free lunchmeat
that their children are getting

1196
01:10:45,229 --> 01:10:48,494
are contaminated
with high levels of mercury.

1197
01:10:48,566 --> 01:10:50,966
Are you aware
of the Mayor of Taiji's plan

1198
01:10:51,035 --> 01:10:52,593
to distribute dolphin meat
throughout Japan

1199
01:10:52,670 --> 01:10:54,160
to Japanese children?

1200
01:10:55,506 --> 01:10:58,805
I think you...
correctly misunderstood.

1201
01:10:58,876 --> 01:10:59,968
Did I?

1202
01:11:00,044 --> 01:11:03,172
You perfectly misunderstood.

1203
01:11:16,127 --> 01:11:18,960
Two city council members
came out on record.

1204
01:11:19,030 --> 01:11:20,657
They risked their...

1205
01:11:20,731 --> 01:11:23,222
if not their lives,
their livelihood to speak out.

1206
01:11:46,324 --> 01:11:48,121
There's a saying in Japan

1207
01:11:48,192 --> 01:11:51,719
that says the nail that sticks out
must be pounded down,

1208
01:11:51,796 --> 01:11:53,127
and so it's a real problem

1209
01:11:53,197 --> 01:11:56,257
just to stand up
and be counted in Japan.

1210
01:11:57,468 --> 01:12:01,734
There's no environmental movement
working actively on this issue

1211
01:12:01,806 --> 01:12:05,469
that has any kind
of power at all in that country.

1212
01:12:05,543 --> 01:12:07,807
We are dumping in the environment

1213
01:12:07,879 --> 01:12:12,179
all kinds of chemicals
like mercury, cadmium, lead.

1214
01:12:12,250 --> 01:12:13,649
We have the obligation...

1215
01:12:13,718 --> 01:12:16,687
We have a moral authority
to do something about it.

1216
01:12:16,754 --> 01:12:17,846
In a few years,

1217
01:12:17,922 --> 01:12:19,719
we may look back
and wonder what we did,

1218
01:12:19,790 --> 01:12:23,726
allowing more and more tons
of meat to be consumed.

1219
01:12:23,794 --> 01:12:25,557
We have a moral obligation,

1220
01:12:25,630 --> 01:12:28,394
and let it not be said
that you didn't know about it.

1221
01:12:28,466 --> 01:12:29,728
You know about it.

1222
01:12:31,202 --> 01:12:35,468
To me, you're either an activist
or an inactivist,

1223
01:12:35,539 --> 01:12:37,234
and I wanted to be active.

1224
01:12:37,308 --> 01:12:39,242
I wanted to stop this.

1225
01:13:17,581 --> 01:13:19,105
I recognize it. Do you?

1226
01:13:19,183 --> 01:13:21,549
8335. Yeah, I do recognize it.

1227
01:13:21,619 --> 01:13:24,144
I think it was the double
channels. Yep.

1228
01:13:25,756 --> 01:13:27,314
Can you go straight?

1229
01:13:28,693 --> 01:13:30,456
They're doing a circle.

1230
01:13:30,528 --> 01:13:31,961
Let's take a quick break.

1231
01:13:32,029 --> 01:13:33,018
Quick, quick, quick, quick.

1232
01:13:33,097 --> 01:13:36,658
- It's 766. It's the cop.
- Is it?

1233
01:15:18,903 --> 01:15:20,928
Louie, Louie, are you there?

1234
01:16:09,220 --> 01:16:10,915
Yeah, that's cool.

1235
01:16:20,498 --> 01:16:21,829
Set it down.

1236
01:20:56,707 --> 01:21:02,202
There was kind of a collective horror
when we started to see the footage.

1237
01:21:02,279 --> 01:21:04,338
It was mind-boggling.

1238
01:21:07,584 --> 01:21:09,142
They're doing it exactly

1239
01:21:09,219 --> 01:21:10,743
like they did with the large whales.

1240
01:21:10,821 --> 01:21:13,449
they're slaughtering
every one they can get.

1241
01:22:03,140 --> 01:22:05,404
Why didn't they set them free?

1242
01:22:10,314 --> 01:22:14,614
That question has kept me
awake for a long time.

1243
01:22:23,994 --> 01:22:25,689
I've watched them give birth.

1244
01:22:25,762 --> 01:22:29,755
I've nursed them back to health
when they're sick.

1245
01:22:31,401 --> 01:22:33,835
Had I known what I know now,

1246
01:22:33,904 --> 01:22:35,337
I would have raised enough money

1247
01:22:35,405 --> 01:22:37,168
to buy them away
from the Seaquarium

1248
01:22:37,241 --> 01:22:38,435
and set them free.

1249
01:22:38,509 --> 01:22:41,000
That would have been
the right thing to do.

1250
01:22:41,078 --> 01:22:44,741
I was buying
a new Porsche every year.

1251
01:22:44,815 --> 01:22:50,515
But I was as ignorant as I could be
for as long as I could be.

1252
01:22:50,587 --> 01:22:54,387
I didn't think about that
for a long time later.

1253
01:23:00,864 --> 01:23:02,058
Listen to me.

1254
01:23:02,132 --> 01:23:05,329
Our killing method
has been improved substantially,

1255
01:23:05,402 --> 01:23:07,495
and the fishermen in Taiji

1256
01:23:07,571 --> 01:23:09,766
